<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_100> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_100" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_71> ;
    del:text """Dar nu trebuie s脛聝 cre脛聝m noi inegalit脛聝脠聸i sau s脛聝 penaliz脛聝m tocmai antreprenorii care au respectat deja standardele europene.
脙聨n propunerea Omnibus vedem m脛聝suri utile, cum ar fi reducerea birocra脠聸iei pentru IMM-uri sau facilitarea achizi脠聸iilor publice pentru companiile europene, dar vedem 脠聶i riscuri majore. Dac脛聝 elimin脛聝m dintr-odat脛聝 raport脛聝rile pentru multe companii, ce facem cu firmele care deja au investit 脙庐n aceste standarde? Dac脛聝 schimb脛聝m regulile de la un an la altul, ce garan脠聸ie mai ofer脛聝 Europa investitorilor? Cine a gre脠聶it: Comisia din mandatul precedent sau cea din mandatul actual? Cine suport脛聝 costurile?
Avem nevoie de o tranzi脠聸ie echilibrat脛聝 care sprijin脛聝 IMM-urile. Europa trebuie s脛聝 fie un model de predictibilitate, nu de reguli care vin 脠聶i pleac脛聝 peste noapte. Da, simplific脛聝m, dar s脛聝 nu introducem noi solu脠聸ii care risc脛聝 s脛聝 afecteze economia noastr脛聝. Trebuie s脛聝 p脛聝str脛聝m valorile sociale 脠聶i totodat脛聝 trebuie s脛聝 ajut脛聝m firmele s脛聝 creasc脛聝. 脙聨n acela脠聶i timp, trebuie s脛聝 spun: nu trebuie s脛聝 facem un pas 脙庐napoi 脙庐n materie de responsabilitate.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T19:32:55"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_101> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_101" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_72> ;
    del:text """Il conviendrait 脙漏galement de mettre en place une avance sur recettes garantie par l芒聙聶Union europ脙漏enne. Cet outil permettrait aux entreprises locales de mieux acc脙漏der aux financements et 脙漏viterait que des projets importants pour le d脙漏veloppement de nos outre-mer ne se retrouvent mort-n脙漏s pour des questions de d脙漏lais de financement.
Il est temps de simplifier les d脙漏marches et d芒聙聶adapter les r脙漏glementations aux r脙漏alit脙漏s ultramarines. L芒聙聶Union europ脙漏enne a choisi d芒聙聶int脙漏grer les r脙漏gions ultramarines depuis脗聽1992, en cr脙漏ant les r脙漏gions ultrap脙漏riph脙漏riques. Elle ne doit pas 脙陋tre un frein, mais un v脙漏ritable soutien 脙聽 leur d脙漏veloppement.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T19:34:09"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_102> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_102" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_73> ;
    del:text """Es insostenible seguir lastrando de esta manera nuestra competitividad en un momento en el que necesitamos, m脙隆s que nunca, competir en un mundo cada vez m脙隆s complejo e inseguro. Y la Comisi脙鲁n hace bien rectificando el camino; sin embargo, nuestras empresas ya han invertido millones para adaptarse a la normativa sobre divulgaci脙鲁n de informaci脙鲁n no financiera脗聽y ahora se preguntan cu脙隆nto m脙隆s tienen que reinvertir para readaptarse de nuevo.
Por ello es vital no retrasar, sino congelar, la aplicaci脙鲁n de estas reglas y trabajar en una nueva norma que sea seria, que d脙漏 certidumbre y seguridad a nuestros sectores productivos, que favorezca la creaci脙鲁n de un ecosistema europeo de peque脙卤as y medianas empresas y empresas emergentes,脗聽que permita la atracci脙鲁n y la retenci脙鲁n del talento y que permita innovar.
Competir no es una opci脙鲁n, por mucho que los socialistas y los verdes digan lo contrario: es una necesidad para mantener nuestro Estado de bienestar y hoy, m脙隆s que nunca, nuestra seguridad.
Pero toda revisi脙鲁n ha de hacerse con cabeza y evaluando su impacto. Si no, por muchas Br脙潞julas que aprobemos, seguiremos perdidos buscando el norte.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T19:36:05"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_103> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_103" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_74> ;
    del:text """Right-wing politics gave us the banking and economic crash, the climate crisis, the rise of homophobia and racism and the vaccine hesitancy that cost lives. It is right-wing policies that fuel homelessness and lead to poorer pay, more discrimination and unsafe work environments. And it is the politics of the right that pours petrol on the conflicts in Ukraine and Gaza.
So we must greet the promotion of 'simplification' and 'cutting red tape' with deep suspicion. Our environmental and social standards were hard fought for. We cannot allow the rest of this Parliament to be driven by a deregulation agenda.
The market has no conscience 芒聙聯 neither, it seems, do those who worship it.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T19:37:17"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_104> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_104" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_75> ;
    del:text """Wenn aber der Ruf der Europ脙陇ischen Union bei den eigenen Unionsb脙录rgerinnen und脗聽芒聙聭b脙录rgern Schaden nimmt aufgrund dieser 脙聹berregulierung, dann ist es h脙露chste Eisenbahn, dass gehandelt wird. Die Europ脙陇ische Kommission muss verstehen, dass der Weg der vergangenen Periode der Holzweg war. Es war falsch, was gemacht wurde. Das Lieferkettengesetz war falsch, es hat nicht meine Zustimmung bekommen hier im Europ脙陇ischen Parlament.
Jetzt, mit der Wortsch脙露pfung Omnibus, soll es dazu kommen, dass dereguliert wird, dass Unternehmen frei arbeiten k脙露nnen, dass der europ脙陇ische Wirtschaftsmarkt sich erholen kann und dass es Zukunft gibt f脙录r 脙聳sterreichs und Europas Unternehmen und Europas Arbeitnehmer.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T19:38:34"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_105> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_105" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_76> ;
    del:text "W ubieg脜聜ym tygodniu uczestniczy脜聜am w wydarzeniu z udzia脜聜em przedstawicieli polskiego przemys脜聜u kosmetycznego, kt脙鲁rzy przedstawili nam 芒聙聻tsunami unijnych regulacji芒聙聺, do kt脙鲁rych musz脛聟 si脛聶 dostosowywa脛聡. Istnieje ponad 300 szczeg脙鲁脜聜owych przepis脙鲁w sektorowych dotycz脛聟cych tylko kosmetyk脙鲁w. Zmieniaj脛聟 si脛聶 tak cz脛聶sto, 脜录e prowadzenie firmy staje si脛聶 nieprzewidywalne. Dlatego ciesz脛聶 si脛聶, widz脛聟c pierwsz脛聟 propozycj脛聶 Omnibusa, i doceniam zaanga脜录owanie przewodnicz脛聟cej von der Leyen w u脜聜atwianie 脜录ycia naszym przedsi脛聶biorcom. Ale deregulacja musi by脛聡 czym脜聸 wi脛聶cej ni脜录 zmian脛聟 przepis脙鲁w na nowe czy odroczeniem ich stosowania. Regulacji musi by脛聡 po prostu radykalnie mniej. Zawalczmy o naszych przedsi脛聶biorc脙鲁w. To oni generuj脛聟 bogactwo Unii Europejskiej. I obud脜潞my si脛聶, 脜录eby nie by脜聜o za p脙鲁脜潞no." ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T19:40:14"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_106> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_106" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_3> ;
    del:text """SMEs represent 99.8脗聽% of all active businesses in Europe, employing nearly 90 million people. In today's volatile times, we cannot afford for our businesses and industries to be the ones to fall behind, suffocated by excessive regulation. From the automotive and energy industries to steel and aluminium, we cannot allow them to be held back by unbalanced green policies and red tape.
The Omnibus package is a final call, a final call for Europe to introduce simpler rules, stronger investments and unlock potential to boost our competitiveness.
Alongside with increased defence spending, the only way forward is to create a more favourable business environment.
The EUR 6 billion that we can cut in annual administrative costs must be reinvested in our innovation, research and development. History will not forgive us if we don't do this step now.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T19:41:59"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_107> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_107" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_77> ;
    del:text """In the current EU political climate, marked by concerns over tariffs, trade tensions and the spectre of Donald Trump, simplification in EU rules have never been more crucial.脗聽The Commissioner's latest simplification package could save our companies EUR脗聽6.3 billion in administrative costs.
However, as we streamline, we must maintain regulatory certainty and clarity. I welcome proposals to revise the scope of the CSRD, reducing heavy burdens on SMEs and enabling them to prioritise innovation.脗聽Yet, simplification cannot compromise our climate commitments. With clear climate targets for 2030 and beyond, the fundamental course of direction is not changing and so regulatory adjustments must reinforce, not weaken our green objectives.
In this context, I have two questions for the Commission. Firstly, will the upcoming agricultural simplification be as ambitious as those in the first Omnibus proposal and can you provide more detail here, please? Secondly, in the context of the EU-UK reset, could you clarify how simplifications within the CBAM may affect alignment with the UK's ETS?""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T19:43:28"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_108> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_108" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_78> ;
    del:text """We zijn geen "market makers" meer. Met name tegen de collega's van de S&D wil ik graag zeggen dat de wereld echt is veranderd. We zijn niet meer de baas. De kracht van onze economie en de concurrentiekracht van onze bedrijven zijn nu essentieel om ons te beschermen en relevant te blijven in de wereld. En dat gaat niet goed.
Het afgelopen mandaat was dit Huis massaproducent van meer wetten en regelgeving, met meer complexiteit: taxonomie, CSRD en CSDDD zijn daar heel goede voorbeelden van. Het is veelzeggend dat er nu wetgeving wordt aangepast die nog niet eens is ingegaan.
Als we onze bedrijven en vooral het MKB niet ontzien, kunnen ze hun positie op de wereldmarkt wel vergeten. Dat is al gebeurd met de staal-, chemie- en cementsector. We moeten vereenvoudigen om concurrerend te blijven. Maar laten we ook eens beginnen met onze bedrijven gewoon te vertrouwen en te verwachten dat ze hun werk goed willen doen.
Uit onderzoek blijkt dat de complexiteit van de regelgeving een van de belangrijkste redenen is voor ondernemers om hun activiteiten stop te zetten. Daarom is deze eerste Omnibus een stap in de goede richting. Ik hoop op een hele serie van Omnibussen. Ons verzet tegen de complexiteit van de regelgeving moet langdurig en vasthoudend zijn, op alle niveaus. Dit is nodig voor onze bestaanzekerheid en om het vertrouwen van ondernemers in het Europese project te herstellen.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T19:45:09"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_109> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_109" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_79> ;
    del:text "A Bizotts脙隆g omnibusz csomagja ez脙漏rt biztat脙鲁 脙漏s j脙鲁 kezdet a kkv-bar脙隆t k脙露rnyezet megteremt脙漏s脙漏re, hiszen a c脙漏gek ak脙隆r 80 sz脙隆zal脙漏k脙隆t mentes脙颅theti a jelent脙漏st脙漏tel al脙鲁l. De gyorsan kell cselekedn脙录nk, mert a v脙隆llalkoz脙隆sok m脙隆r dolgoznak az ESG elv脙隆r脙隆soknak val脙鲁 megfelel脙漏sen, nagy er脜聭forr脙隆sok 脙隆r脙隆n. 2025-ben csak Magyarorsz脙隆gon ez a kih脙颅v脙隆s t脙露bb t脙颅zezer kkv-t 脙漏rint. Az egyszer脜卤s脙颅t脙漏s mellett fontos, hogy a szab脙隆lyokat a v脙隆llalkoz脙隆sok meg is 脙漏rts脙漏k. Ha m脙隆r omnibusz csomagr脙鲁l besz脙漏l脙录nk, 脙漏rtse meg a Clapham-omnibuszon utaz脙鲁 h脙漏tk脙露znapi ember is. 脜聬 ugyanis az angol jogrendszerben haszn脙隆lt 脙隆tlagember m脙漏rc脙漏je. Hagyjunk teh脙隆t leveg脜聭t a v脙隆llalkoz脙隆sainknak, hogy ne csak t脙潞l脙漏ljenek, hanem boldoguljanak is. Ha 脜聭k sikeresek, Eur脙鲁pa is az." ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T19:46:56"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_11> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_11" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_5> ;
    del:text """The right to be who you are, to love who you want and to live your life free from discrimination is a fundamental European right. That right is clearly under attack.
At this critical moment, the decision by the European Commission to announce the withdrawal of the horizontal anti-discrimination directive came as a shock. It also represents a betrayal of all the EU citizens who are currently lacking protection against discrimination.
It is time for the EU to show global leadership against discrimination, not to back down. As the European Parliament's rapporteur for this directive, I strongly condemn this decision and I urge the European Commission to immediately reconsider it.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T17:12:01"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_110> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_110" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_80> ;
    del:text """Kolege s lijeve strane, vi ka脜戮ete, ne treba nam omnibus paket. Pa ka脜戮ite to tim ljudima koji svakog dana moraju prona脛聡i novac kako bi imali za proizvodnju, kako bi mogli platiti svoje radnike. Naravno da omnibus paketom ne脛聡emo sve rije脜隆iti, ali 脛聡emo osloboditi vrijeme i resurse koji su sada zarobljeni u beskrajnoj papirologiji, birokratskim labirintima i prekomjernom administrativnom optere脛聡enju.
Tako 脛聡emo omogu脛聡iti tvrtkama ono o 脛聧emu govorimo, 脜隆to imaju SAD, 脜隆to imaju neke druge razvijenije zemlje, a mi nemamo, a to je: inovacije, rast i konkurentnost.
I zaklju脛聧it 脛聡u, pojednostavljenje nije samo sebi svrha. Ono je alat za ja脛聧anje na脜隆ih poduzetnika i ostvarivanje sna脜戮nijeg, konkurentnijeg i otpornijeg europskog tr脜戮i脜隆ta.
To ne smije biti ideolo脜隆ko pitanje. To je pitanje razuma.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T19:48:51"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_111> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_111" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_81> ;
    del:text """脠聵i, doamna comisar脛聝, suprareglementarea poate s脛聝 duc脛聝 la 脠聶tergerea locurilor de munc脛聝. Trebuie s脛聝 脙庐n脠聸elegem, am lucrat mult mai mult 脙庐n economie, 脙庐n industrie dec脙垄t 脙庐n politic脛聝, trebuie s脛聝 脙庐n脠聸elegem c脛聝 trebuie s脛聝 trat脛聝m la pachet drepturile lucr脛聝torilor, cu condi脠聸ii pentru IMM-uri, mai ales, 脠聶i pentru companii, pentru c脛聝 doar companiile creeaz脛聝 locuri de munc脛聝 脠聶i dac脛聝 reglement脛聝m, suprareglement脛聝m, pot s脛聝 se erodeze aceste locuri de munc脛聝.
Dar 脠聶i dac脛聝 dereglement脛聝m, putem s脛聝 ajungem pe termen lung s脛聝 erod脛聝m locurile de munc脛聝.
De aceea trebuie o analiz脛聝 foarte bun脛聝, 脠聶i poate vina cea mai mare pe care o are Uniunea European脛聝, Comisia European脛聝, este aceea c脛聝 se fac reglement脛聝ri care se bat cap 脙庐n cap. 脠聵i un agricultor, un fermier, o IMM nu mai 脠聶tie ce s脛聝 fac脛聝 脙庐n momentul 脙庐n care apar 脙庐n conflict aceste legisla脠聸ii.
De aceea, trebuie cu foarte mare aten脠聸ie s脛聝 analiz脛聝m ce dereglement脛聝m 脠聶i mai ales, s脛聝 nu mai ad脛聝ug脛聝m birocra脠聸ie care nu aduce nimic, nici competitivitate, nici siguran脠聸a locului de munc脛聝, nici sustenabilitate, nici posibilitatea companiilor de a m脛聝ri salariile.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T19:50:10"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_112> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_112" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_82> ;
    del:text "Ik roep de Commissie dan ook op om de komende tijd meer ambitie te tonen. Dit is een heel goed voorstel, maar het gaat nog niet ver genoeg. U bevindt zich op een betere weg. Zoals we in Nederland zeggen: \"Beter ten halve gekeerd dan ten hele gedwaald\". Ik wens u daarbij heel veel succes." ;
