<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_165> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_165" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_121> ;
    del:text """We have faced various crises 芒聙聯 one after the other 芒聙聯 and every time we have proven that we are stronger when tested. We have delivered vaccines to our citizens in record time; we secured gas supplies when Russia cut them off; we tackled economic turmoil. And every time there was talk about disunity, we proved we can succeed.
Today we face yet another situation, where our closest ally often sounds like an adversary, and that makes us feel threatened and uncertain. And at the beginning of this plenary, I want us to remember the words of Robert Schuman, who said: 'Europe will not be made at once [...]. It will be built through concrete achievements which first create a de facto solidarity'. It is the moment of solidarity where words turn into actions, because words do not build Europe.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T21:19:18"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_166> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_166" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_71> ;
    del:text """脙聨n ultimii ani, prin activitatea mea din Parlamentul European, am salvat miliarde de euro din fondurile neutilizate, modific脙垄nd regulamentele europene pentru a faza proiectele europene. Am contribuit la simplificarea regulilor privind accesarea programelor europene 脠聶i am amendat bugetul Uniunii Europene pentru ca aceste resurse s脛聝 ajung脛聝 脙庐n regiunea noastr脛聝.
Dar aceste fonduri nu sunt doar cifre pe h脙垄rtie. Trebuie s脛聝 privim 脙庐nainte: avem nevoie de o absorb脠聸ie mai bun脛聝, mai eficient脛聝, mai mult脛聝 flexibilitate 脠聶i o strategie pentru viitor.
100 de miliarde de euro sunt un succes, dar 脠聶i o responsabilitate. Extremismul caut脛聝 s脛聝 distrug脛聝 aceasta oportunitate pentru Rom脙垄nia.
Voi continua s脛聝 lupt pentru ca fiecare euro s脛聝 fie folosit acolo unde este cel mai necesar pentru rom脙垄ni 脠聶i europeni.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T21:20:48"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_167> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_167" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_122> ;
    del:text """Na Uni脙拢o Europeia, enfrentamos desafios semelhantes. Temos o direito de saber para onde vai o dinheiro dos nossos contribuintes, que projetos s脙拢o financiados, quem beneficia dos fundos europeus destinados 脙聽 Ajuda P脙潞blica ao Desenvolvimento.
Que think tanks, que 脙鲁rg脙拢os de comunica脙搂脙拢o social foram financiados pela Comiss脙拢o Europeia? Que pol脙颅tica estamos, sem saber, a subsidiar?脗聽Sem respostas claras, a confian脙搂a nas institui脙搂脙碌es europeias 脙漏 abalada e a democracia, enfraquecida.
脙聣 imperativo criar um Departamento Europeu para a Efici脙陋ncia Governamental. Este organismo vai garantir que cada euro 脙漏 gasto de forma transparente e respons脙隆vel, assegurando que os financiamentos n脙拢o servem interesses ocultos, mas, sim, o bem comum.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T21:22:12"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_168> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_168" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_114> ;
    del:text """Abuzul electoral, interzicerea unor cet脛聝脠聸eni de a candida 脠聶i 脙庐mpiedicarea unei p脛聝turi importante a societ脛聝脠聸ii de a-脠聶i exercita dreptul legitim de vot, par s脛聝 fi devenit noua regul脛聝 din Rom脙垄nia.
Prin cenzura electoral脛聝, autorit脛聝脠聸ile rom脙垄ne au reu脠聶it performan脠聸a de a inflama popula脠聸ia, cre脙垄nd tensiune maxim脛聝 脙庐ntr-o societate 脙庐n care milioane de oameni se simt ast脛聝zi ne脙庐ndrept脛聝脠聸i脠聸i 脠聶i neasculta脠聸i. Cum pot s脛聝 mai aib脛聝 rom脙垄nii 脙庐ncredere 脙庐n democra脠聸ie sau 脙庐n justi脠聸ie? Acest co脠聶mar trebuie s脛聝 脙庐nceteze. Trebuie s脛聝 revenim imediat la valorile democratice 脠聶i la libertate.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T21:23:28"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_169> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_169" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_123> ;
    del:text """Many of the citizens that voted for their countries to enter the Union after the 1990s did so with the hope that their countries and societies will converge to these European values.
What we are seeing in the Commission work programme is that the anti-discrimination directive 芒聙聯 and many other measures for which we did not reach an agreement in five years 芒聙聯 gets withdrawn.
This means that the Council gets handed the perfect weapon: if they ever think that we're asking for too much in the Parliament or in the Commission, they just need to drag their feet for long enough and then make the problem disappear.
In the meantime, the message we are sending to Europeans is clear: these values you hoped for will remain unreachable.
It is unacceptable that we allow a couple of holdout countries to prevent the adoption of European rules that deal with values central to the European project. We need to be looking immediately at another proposal for horizontal rules to combat discrimination.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T21:25:14"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_17> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_17" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1> ;
    del:text """In accordance with Rule 9(9), the following report is added to the final draft agenda for a vote on Tuesday: report by Dainius 脜陆alimas脗聽on the request for waiver of the immunity of Adam Bielan.
With the agreement of the political groups, I also wish to put to the House the following proposal for changes to the final draft agenda for Tuesday. The order of debates in the afternoon will change as follows.
The debate on the presentation of the proposal for a Critical Medicines Act will be taken as the second point, and the debate on the presentation of the proposal on a new common approach on returns will be taken as the third point.
If there are no objections to this, then the change will be approved.
We now move to changes requested by the political groups, starting with Wednesday.
The ECR Group has requested that Council and Commission statements on 'Recent events in Romania: the ongoing investigation into the presidential candidate' be added as the fifth point in the afternoon, before the debate on frozen Russian assets. As a consequence, the sitting would be extended to 11脗聽p.m.
I give the floor to Gheorghe Piperea to move the request on behalf of the ECR.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T17:16:22"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_170> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_170" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_124> ;
    del:text """Es una amenaza comercial muy grave, porque esta guerra arancelaria tampoco tiene en Europa qui脙漏n la defienda, se脙卤ora comisaria. 脗驴Qu脙漏 est脙隆 haciendo la Uni脙鲁n Europea para potenciar sus propios astilleros y la industria auxiliar local? Nada.
Desde el BNG hemos defendido durante muchos a脙卤os que se potenciara y apoyara la industria europea con ayudas p脙潞blicas. En el caso de la industria galega, hemos defendido que da trabajo a muchos miles de trabajadores y esta industria ha sufrido recortes, reconversiones, limitaciones de producci脙鲁n y competencia desleal. Y, el 脙潞ltimo clavo que faltaba, la imposici脙鲁n de aranceles a una industria que es exportadora. 脗驴Qu脙漏 va a hacer la Uni脙鲁n Europea para defender al sector del metal?""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T21:26:32"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_171> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_171" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_7> ;
    del:text """Let us be very clear: Ireland's neutrality and our long-standing commitment to UN peacekeeping missions has made the world safer. It is attacks on the UN and on neutrality that is making the world less safe.
From our role in leading negotiations on the Treaty of the Non-Proliferation of Nuclear Weapons to being the only country to have an unbroken record of UN peacekeeping service since 1958, Ireland's neutrality has been a beacon in this world.
The cynical moves to scrap the triple lock will move us away from the UN and threatens Ireland's neutrality. The most recent poll shows that 75脗聽% of Irish people support our continued neutrality. Yet the Irish Government seems determined to throw its lot in with the EU, to undermine our neutrality at every turn, while the EU is engaging in an arms race. It's time to save the triple lock.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T21:27:57"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_172> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_172" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_125> ;
    del:text "Europa w ten spos脙鲁b traci konkurencyjno脜聸脛聡 i poza tym oddaje si脛聶 polityce klimatycznej, kt脙鲁ra do niczego nie doprowadzi. Bo co z tego, 脜录e my ograniczamy co roku zu脜录ycie w脛聶gla, skoro ca脜聜y 脜聸wiat jeszcze wi脛聶cej go zu脜录ywa? Przecie脜录 nie jeste脜聸my otoczeni 脜录adn脛聟 szklan脛聟 kopu脜聜脛聟. No i prosz脛聶 spojrze脛聡 te脜录, jak to wygl脛聟da. Pani przewodnicz脛聟ca von der Leyen by脜聜a ostatnio w Indiach, zapowiada脜聜a wsp脙鲁脜聜prac脛聶 handlow脛聟 z Indiami, z Indiami, kt脙鲁re stoj脛聟 na w脛聶glu, czyli u nas zamykamy kopalnie po to, 脜录eby importowa脛聡 rzeczy z kraj脙鲁w, kt脙鲁re tego w脛聶gla jeszcze wi脛聶cej zu脜录ywaj脛聟 ni脜录 wcze脜聸niej. To jest 脜聸mieszne. I ten ca脜聜y Zielony 脜聛ad nadaje si脛聶 tylko do kosza." ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T21:29:13"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_173> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_173" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_105> ;
    del:text """Eine Studie von R脙录stungslobbyisten aus Deutschland mit dem bezeichnenden Namen脗聽Sparta gibt dar脙录ber nun Auskunft. Es geht um die Schaffung einer 芒聙聻asymmetrischen 脙聹berlegenheit芒聙聹. Es geht um 芒聙聻digitale F脙录hrungs脙录berlegenheit, Aufkl脙陇rungs芒聙聭 und Wirk脙录berlegenheit, die sofort verf脙录gbar und kurzfristig einsetzbar sein sollen芒聙聹.
Mit Landesverteidigung hat dies ganz offensichtlich nichts mehr zu tun. Auch nicht mit einem Gleichgewicht der milit脙陇rischen Kr脙陇fte und noch weniger mit der strukturellen Nichtangriffsf脙陇higkeit, wie sie die NATO fr脙录her f脙录r sich postuliert hat. Hier soll der Krieg als Mittel der Politik wieder hoff脙陇hig gemacht werden. Daf脙录r hat die Europ脙陇ische Union sicherlich nicht den Friedensnobelpreis erhalten.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T21:30:34"^^xsd:dateTime .

