<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_50> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_50" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_28> ;
    del:text """Autrement, vous avez le choix de ne pas faire cette n脙漏gociation avec nous, mais avec l芒聙聶extr脙陋me droite. Si vous n脙漏gociez avec l芒聙聶extr脙陋me droite, alors cela veut dire que vous cassez la capacit脙漏 脙聽 avoir une confiance dans cette majorit脙漏 von脗聽der脗聽Leyen, qui a 脙漏lu la pr脙漏sidente de la Commission. Or vous avez besoin de cette majorit脙漏 von脗聽der脗聽Leyen; l芒聙聶Europe a besoin de cette majorit脙漏 von der Leyen pour r脙漏pondre 脙聽 la crise g脙漏opolitique que nous connaissons et construire cette Europe-puissance dont on a plus que jamais besoin. Ce n芒聙聶est pas avec l芒聙聶extr脙陋me droite que vous allez le faire. Ce n芒聙聶est pas avec ceux qui viennent de rappeler que la pire responsabilit脙漏 sur le secteur de l芒聙聶acier, ce serait le texte sur la CSRD, alors que ce sont 脙漏videmment les amis de l芒聙聶extr脙陋me droite, comme Donald脗聽Trump, qui veulent imposer des droits de douane qui vont faire tr脙篓s mal au secteur de l芒聙聶acier.
Vous avez le choix: soit vous faites une simplification intelligente avec nous, soit vous faites la tron脙搂onneuse avec l芒聙聶extr脙陋me droite. C芒聙聶est l芒聙聶Histoire qui vous regarde.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T18:10:53"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_51> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_51" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_20> ;
    del:text """Oui, nous avons besoin de simplifier et nous le dirons tous ici aujourd芒聙聶hui. Cependant, vous ne simplifiez pas; vous avez d脙漏cid脙漏 d芒聙聶emprunter 脙聽 tombeau ouvert l芒聙聶autoroute de la d脙漏r脙漏gulation. Ce faisant, vous mettez 脙聽 mal notre souverainet脙漏, nos valeurs et la transition vers une 脙漏conomie responsable, parce que,脗聽en d脙漏faisant ce que nous avions commenc脙漏 脙聽 construire, vous d脙漏couragez et vous sanctionnez les entreprises et les investisseurs responsables qui ont d脙漏j脙聽 engag脙漏 le changement. Pour r脙漏sumer, vous sanctionnez la vertu et vous encouragez le vice.
Vous osez 脙漏crire que les entreprises qui ne respecteront pas leurs obligations climatiques, Madame la Commissaire, pourront poursuivre leurs activit脙漏s en toute tranquillit脙漏. Faut-il vraiment encourager les activit脙漏s climaticides? Vous avez 脙漏galement pour objectif de r脙漏duire de 90脗聽% le nombre d芒聙聶entreprises concern脙漏es par des obligations de transparence, dont des secteurs 脙聽 haut risque, comme l芒聙聶industrie mini脙篓re. Est-ce vraiment raisonnable? Non.
Nous ne sommes pas dupes. Si vous choisissez effectivement l芒聙聶alliance avec l芒聙聶extr脙陋me droite, vous ferez le choix non pas de r脙漏duire la bureaucratie, mais bien d芒聙聶脙漏tendre sans limite le domaine de l芒聙聶impunit脙漏. Cette politique, nous la combattrons.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T18:12:48"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_52> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_52" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_29> ;
    del:text """Je vous imagine 脙聽 la Commission europ脙漏enne: la plan脙篓te est en train de cramer 脙聽 +脗聽4脗聽脗掳C, les multinationales continuent d芒聙聶engranger des profits en violant les droits de l芒聙聶homme, et l脙聽 vous vous dites: 脗芦Eur脙陋ka! D脙漏barrassons-nous des seules r脙漏gulations qui existent pour demander des comptes aux entreprises!脗禄
Avec ce paquet 脗芦omnibus脗禄, vous offrez un blanc-seing aux entreprises qui vont d脙漏truire la plan脙篓te et exploiter les travailleurs. Vous jetez le devoir de vigilance des multinationales 脙聽 la poubelle, en limitant la responsabilit脙漏 aux seuls partenaires directs, trahissant son principe m脙陋me, et en supprimant les sanctions financi脙篓res. Tant pis si des entreprises comme Shein, Total ou Vinci continuent all脙篓grement de violer les droits de l芒聙聶homme et de d脙漏truire l芒聙聶environnement en toute impunit脙漏.
Aussi longtemps que nous serons ici, vous pouvez compter sur mon groupe pour se battre afin de prot脙漏ger ces r脙漏glementations et d芒聙聶emp脙陋cher les multinationales de faire leur loi et de g脙漏n脙漏rer des profits au d脙漏triment de nos vies.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T18:14:50"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_53> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_53" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_30> ;
    del:text """Je脜聸li naprawd脛聶 chcemy uwolni脛聡 biznes, potrzebujemy pi脜聜y 脜聜a脜聞cuchowej, takiej, jak ma prezydent Milei, a nie no脜录yka do papieru. Je脜录eli m脙鲁wimy o harmonizacji regulacji, to oznacza, 脜录e zamiast trzech dokument脙鲁w b脛聶dziemy mieli jedn脛聟, ale za to napisan脛聟 bardzo ma脜聜脛聟 czcionk脛聟. To nie jest 脜录adne rozwi脛聟zanie.
Komisja Europejska m脙鲁wi o uproszczeniach, ale jednocze脜聸nie wprowadza i podtrzymuje Zielony 脜聛ad, ESG i kolejne normy. To tak, jakby kaza脛聡 komu脜聸 biec sprint z ci脛聶脜录kim plecakiem pe脜聜nym kamieni, ale obieca脛聡 mu, 脜录e dostanie nowe sznur脙鲁wki. To nic nie zmieni. Je脜录eli godzimy si脛聶 na to, 脜录e z ESG ma by脛聡 zwolnione 80% firm, to dlaczego nie zwolni脛聡 pozosta脜聜ych 20%? Po co w og脙鲁le firmy maj脛聟 raportowa脛聡 te wszystkie rzeczy? To jest kompletnie zb脛聶dny ci脛聶脜录ar i powinni脜聸my zacz脛聟脛聡 od zawieszenia tego, 脜录eby pokaza脛聡, 脜录e przynajmniej m脙鲁wimy realnie o jakiej脜聸 deregulacji.
Bo problemem nie jest z脜聜o脜录ono脜聸脛聡 przepis脙鲁w, problemem jest ich liczba. Nie potrzebujemy przepis脙鲁w o tym, jak upraszcza脛聡 przepisy. Potrzebujemy, 脜录eby Unia Europejska przesta脜聜a tworzy脛聡 nowe przepisy. Ju脜录 teraz mamy wszyscy dosy脛聡 papierologii, a uzyskujemy kolejne obowi脛聟zki. Z tym sobie poradz脛聟 du脜录e korporacje, ale nie poradz脛聟 sobie wszystkie ma脜聜e przedsi脛聶biorstwa, kt脙鲁re po prostu z tymi obowi脛聟zkami nie wyrabiaj脛聟.
Musimy powa脜录nie si脛聶 wzi脛聟脛聡 za ci脛聶cie regulacji, za zaprzestanie tworzenia nowych przepis脙鲁w i wtedy b脛聶dziemy rzeczywi脜聸cie m脙鲁wi脛聡 o zdejmowaniu tej czerwonej ta脜聸my z Unii Europejskiej.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T18:16:15"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_54> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_54" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_31> ;
    del:text """The strong simplification dimension of the 2025 Commission work programme and our first Omnibus proposals, which we presented at the end of last month.
Allow me to begin with the bigger picture. The world is changing in front of our eyes. We see dramatic shifts in the geopolitical landscape. We need to treat these developments as a call to action. The freedoms that we enjoy and the values that we cherish can no longer be taken for granted in a complex and more conflictual world.
For the EU, they also depend on maintaining and further developing our economic base by adapting, innovating and competing in the world. This is why the Commission has prioritised enhancing Europe's competitiveness in this new mandate. Cutting red tape is an important element of building that competitive Europe. We have set out ambitious targets for administrative costs, reducing them by 25脗聽% for all companies and 35脗聽% for SMEs, all while ensuring cost effective delivery of the underlying policy priorities.
This translates into cutting roughly EUR 37.5 billion in annual administrative costs by the end of this Commission's mandate.脗聽And in the end, more innovation and investment will bring prosperity and wealth for our citizens.
Put simply, we cannot hope to successfully compete in a perilous world with one hand behind our backs.
I want to be very clear that we remain deeply committed to building a greener and fairer society and economy. Simplification is about making sure that EU rules help deliver, rather than impede, the achievement of our economic, social, environmental and security goals, and bring wealth and prosperity to our citizens. It is about achieving those goals in a smarter and less burdensome way.
Less bureaucracy means more innovation and investment that will secure our long-term prosperity. It means creating new and quality jobs for European workers.
Our Communication on implementation and simplification outlines a comprehensive set of tools to sharpen the quality of our regulatory framework, and to deliver on our agreed objectives. It is constructed around four building blocks: ensuring EU policies deliver results, making Europe simpler and faster, improving the way we make new rules and strengthening our work with co-legislators and stakeholders.
Taken together, it signals a change in the regulatory culture of the European Commission, focussed on making sure that EU rules are as simple and cost effective as possible while they deliver on the ground.
We are already translating the principles of this second bloc into concrete actions, starting with those announced in the 2025 Commission work programme. 11 out of the 18 new initiatives in the work programme aim at simplification and they are complemented by 37 fitness checks and evaluations, which will in turn feed future simplification work.
The main simplification proposals for 2025 are the following:
芒聙聭 A脗聽first Omnibus proposal on sustainability reporting, which we already presented last month, and to which I will return in a moment.
芒聙聭 Investment simplification. Facilitating the deployment and reporting of InvestEU and the European Fund for Strategic Investments, a package including a new definition of small mid-caps so that they can benefit from more targeted, proportionate requirements.
芒聙聭脗聽A digital package to ensure a simplified and more agile means to facilitate once-only reporting, to avoid duplications.
芒聙聭 A proposal to reduce complexity and administrative burden for farmers and national administrations in the context of the Common Agricultural Policy, and.
芒聙聭 The Omnibus脗聽proposal to further simply rules in the defence sector.
As I have mentioned, the Commission already presented the first two Omnibus proposals to simplify EU rules at the end of last month. The Omnibus package covers a far reaching simplification in the fields of sustainability reporting, sustainability, due diligence and taxonomy. The Omnibus package on investment simplification facilitates, amongst others, the deployment and reporting of InvestEU and the European Fund for Strategic investments, and simplifies reporting.
Briefly, these proposals provide for a stop-the-clock proposal to delay the application of the Corporate Sustainability Reporting Directive for companies that have not started reporting yet, freeing around 80脗聽% of companies currently under the scope of CSRD from mandatory reporting requirements and protecting them from excessive information requests by large companies,
They make taxonomy reporting more proportionate by limiting mandatory reporting only to very large companies.
They provide for a major simplification to the carbon border adjustment mechanism that limits obligations for approximately 182脗聽000, or 90脗聽% of importers, most of which are SMEs.
These first two Omnibus packages mark a strong start to delivering our simplification agenda. A conservative estimate puts the annual savings stemming from these two packages at EUR 6.3 billion.
To conclude, honourable Members, as you can see, this Commission is firmly committed to improving implementation and delivering simpler and more cost-efficient rules. We hope to count on your support so that we can deliver fast and sustained changes on the ground in the coming months and years. I will stop here and look forward to our discussion.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T18:18:40"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_55> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_55" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_32> ;
    del:text """Estes d脙漏fices, de facto, existem. Mas hoje quero falar-vos de excessos: a Europa tem excesso de regula脙搂脙拢o, de percentagens e de debate inconsequente.
Nos 脙潞ltimos anos, o PPE, o PSD e eu pr脙鲁pria temos alertado para o excesso regulat脙鲁rio que estrangula a capacidade das empresas europeias de investir, criar empregos e gerar riqueza. Finalmente, temos relat脙鲁rios que nos d脙拢o raz脙拢o e um ambiente pol脙颅tico que nos d脙隆 芒聙聰 a todos 芒聙聰 a oportunidade de fazer diferente.
Por outro lado, h脙隆 excesso de percentagens no discurso pol脙颅tico. Falamos de 99,8脗聽% de PME na Europa, esquecendo que isto representa 26 milh脙碌es de empresas. Referimo-nos a 52脗聽% de valor acrescentado das PME, mas esquecemo-nos de que, por detr脙隆s, est脙拢o 90 milh脙碌es de trabalhadores. N脙鲁s n脙拢o temos de decidir para as percentagens, temos de agir para as pessoas.
Finalmente, temos excesso de debate inconsequente. Um debate alimentado por uma esquerda que acusa a Comiss脙拢o de querer matar o Green Deal quando foi a mesma presidente da Comiss脙拢o quem o lan脙搂ou e por uma extrema芒聙聭direita que脗聽na Europa s脙鲁 v脙陋 o 脙潞nico alvo para alimentar a sua propaganda.
N脙鲁s aqui estamos, como sempre estivemos, no espa脙搂o da modera脙搂脙拢o. Naquele espa脙搂o que aprovou o Green Deal e que quer libertar recursos para as empresas o poderem cumprir. O espa脙搂o que quer que as empresas invistam e criem emprego e n脙拢o se percam em burocracias. O espa脙搂o que quer simplificar a vida a quem gera riqueza e facilitar a vida de quem trabalha.
To conclude, Ms Bischoff and dear Pascal, the EPP is ready to work with everyone 芒聙聯 with everyone. We are just not ready to destroy whatever is left of our European competitiveness.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T18:25:33"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_56> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_56" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_33> ;
    del:text """Se o problema 脙漏 a burocracia que atinge as pequenas e m脙漏dias empresas, porque 脙漏 que n脙拢o se facilita a vida 脙聽s pequenas e m脙漏dias empresas e se opta, por outro lado, por atribuir a empresas que n脙拢o s脙拢o pequenas e m脙漏dias empresas, nomeadamente as designadas small mid芒聙聭caps, o mesmo tratamento que 脙聽s PME?
Essas s脙拢o op脙搂脙碌es erradas, que escondem um problema de fundo que a senhora deputada devia explicar: a forma como este pacote Omnibus verdadeiramente favorece as grandes multinacionais e as grandes empresas, em vez de contribuir para os objetivos que lhe servem de pretexto.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T18:27:52"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_57> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_57" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_32> ;
    del:text """Eu posso responder-lhe o seguinte: esta proposta d脙隆 resposta 脙聽quilo que tem sido um equil脙颅brio necess脙隆rio e uma lideran脙搂a da Uni脙拢o Europeia. E esse equil脙颅brio est脙隆 em encontrarmos capacidade e respostas, em entregar resultados para o ambiente e para a economia. N脙鲁s s脙鲁 podemos ir ao encontro dos des脙颅gnios do ambiente se tivermos o nosso tecido econ脙鲁mico capacitado para o fazer.
E, para terminar, n脙鲁s temos um modelo social europeu para pagar e s脙鲁 脙漏 poss脙颅vel pagarmos esse modelo social com mais competitividade, com mais crescimento econ脙鲁mico e aliviando a carga burocr脙隆tica das nossas PME.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T18:28:36"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_58> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_58" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_34> ;
    del:text """What's not to like, you would think? After all, with the current economic backdrop, efforts to simplify, digitise, streamline, those are to be welcomed and we as a Group could certainly see room for doing that.脗聽But I will tell you what's not to like and that this is not the simplification of EU rules. This is the simplification of a debate. It's an oversimplification of a debate and it's a harmful one.
What we're presented here with is removing liability from a law that says to check and address things like child labour and deforestation. Now, clearly that's not simplification, that's obstructing justice. That's purposefully making things harder for the victims of wrongdoing and NGOs. That's making a mockery of EU law, essentially.脗聽Liability is not just there for the sake of it. It's there to guarantee fairness and a level playing field between cowboy companies and companies that give a damn.
Also, asking companies to only check their direct suppliers, that's pointless box-ticking for companies. You're asking them to look at places where there's no issues and no risks, and you're giving them a blank cheque to ignore risks that are further down their supply chain. Another example: banning companies from requesting information from companies of less than 1脗聽000脗聽employees. That will just mean that their reporting is going to be inaccurate, incomplete and very difficult to comply.
And now we talk about red tape. Make no mistake, this is regulatory schizophrenia that's going to end up increasing compliance costs. Companies have already invested in sustainability and now the Commission is pulling the rug from underneath their feet.脗聽I think this is the kind of nonsense that can only be come up with when people go on what must be an ideological crusade, and that at breakneck speed, refusing to consider real evidence or with a public consultation.
Truly, the European Commission should be ashamed of this proposal. It claims that this is the middle ground, that it's a sensible proposal that is sorely needed, but it is an extreme proposal, let's be clear on that. It radically slashes human rights and environmental standards, and it actually makes things more complicated. And what's more, this is a dishonest reading of what the Draghi report has called for.
No company is leaving the EU because of sustainability reporting. Could things be improved? Yes, of course, let's have a sensible conversation about that. But there's no company that risks bankruptcy unless we tell them that it's okay to have children make their products. This House now has a responsibility to get things back on track, to deliver actual simplification.
Unfortunately, the EPP has already been mind-blowingly open about their willingness to work here with the extreme right, and that's not even plan B for the EPP, it seems that's plan A. The Commission has been absolutely fine to present its proposal under these circumstances. They knew that this couldn't gain a pro-European majority in this form, but it went ahead anyway.脗聽It's time to call this out for what it is. It's an extreme proposal. It's blatantly misguided and it's backed by the fossil fuel industry and the far right.
(The speaker agreed to take a blue-card question)""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T18:29:30"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_59> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_59" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_35> ;
    del:text "And my question is 芒聙聯 to S&D 芒聙聯 you ask to work with us, we are ready to work with everybody here. But the question is, what is S&D actually ready to change in the current proposals? What is it?" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T18:33:17"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_6> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_6" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1> ;
    del:text """The first is on employment protection for the activities of police officers, military personnel, prison officers, and customs and border officials, classifying them as high-risk occupations in the EU. The proposal is referred to the Committee on Employment and Social Affairs.
The second is on the need to extend the period for implementation of the Recovery and Resilience Facility. This proposal is referred to the Committee on Budgets and the Committee on Economic and Monetary Affairs, as committees responsible, and to the Committee on Employment, the Committee on the Environment, the Committee on Industry, Research and Energy and the Committee on Transport and Tourism, for opinion.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T17:06:33"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_60> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_60" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_34> ;
    del:text """But when it comes to what we could actually do to simplify, there's many things that we could be discussing reasonably, but there hasn't been time for that because of a PR stunt from the European Commission that insists on proposing things within the first 100 days.
I don't think there's any necessity to rush things like that and, therefore, we're now faced with proposals that are misguided. I think it's a little bit like saying that if you're driving on the motorway, cars will be able to drive faster without speed limits. That's certainly true, but you're also going to have collisions.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T18:34:21"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_61> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_61" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_36> ;
    del:text """Az omnibusz 1. 脙漏s 2. t脙潞l k脙漏s脜聭n j脙露tt 脙漏s kev脙漏s. Annyi t脙露rt脙漏nik, hogy kozmetik脙隆zni pr脙鲁b脙隆lj脙隆k a kor脙隆bbi balfog脙隆sokat. Mi, a jobboldalon, az 脙录zleti 脙漏rdekk脙漏pviseletekkel k脙露z脙露sen sz脙鲁ltunk, hogy rossz az ir脙隆ny. 脙聳n脙露k 脙隆rtottak Eur脙鲁p脙隆nak, 脙聳n脙露k eur脙鲁paellenesek. Hab脙隆r a javaslat egyszer脜卤s脙颅teni pr脙鲁b脙隆l, az amb脙颅ci脙鲁szint elmarad a sz脙录ks脙漏gest脜聭l. A sz脙漏p脙漏szeti beavatkoz脙隆sokn脙隆l t脙露bbre van sz脙录ks脙漏g. Azt kellene megn脙漏zni, melyek szab脙隆lyoz脙隆si oldalr脙鲁l a f脜聭 probl脙漏m脙隆k, teh脙隆t mi akad脙隆lyozza legink脙隆bb a c脙漏geket abban, hogy forr脙隆shoz jussanak, fejlesszenek 脙漏s az alaptev脙漏kenys脙漏g脙录kre koncentr脙隆lhassanak jelent脙漏sirk脙隆l脙隆s helyett.
Nem ny脙潞lnak el脙漏gg脙漏 b脙隆tran a taxon脙鲁mi脙隆hoz, teh脙隆t tov脙隆bbra is ideol脙鲁giai alapon diszkrimin脙隆lnak befektet脙漏sek k脙露z脙露tt. Marad a z脙露ld ideol脙鲁gia, s 脙潞jra le fogja gy脜聭zni a versenyk脙漏pess脙漏get. A forr脙隆shoz jut脙隆s persze az脙隆ltal is javulna, ha 脙聳n脙露k politikai okokb脙鲁l nem tartan脙隆k vissza az 脙漏n haz脙隆mt脙鲁l is az uni脙鲁s forr脙隆sokat. Az Uni脙鲁ban nem nevelni kell egym脙隆st, hanem k脙露z脙露sen dolgozni a prosperit脙隆s脙漏rt. Sajnos 脙聳n脙露k ez ellen is tesznek. Az eur脙鲁pai v脙隆llalkoz脙隆sok enn脙漏l t脙露bbet 脙漏rdemelnek. Val脙鲁di 脙录zletbar脙隆t fordulatra van sz脙录ks脙漏g, igazi tehercs脙露kkent脙漏ssel. Mi, patri脙鲁t脙隆k ez脙漏rt fogunk dolgozni.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T18:35:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_62> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_62" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_37> ;
    del:text """I numeri parlano da soli: 80 miliardi di euro l'anno spesi solo dalle piccole e medie imprese italiane per adempiere a procedure amministrative. Se consideriamo anche l'impatto sulle famiglie e sulle aziende, la cifra supera i 225 miliardi di euro: l'Europa non pu脙虏 permetterselo; l'Italia non pu脙虏 permetterselo.
Il primo pacchetto Omnibus rappresenta un riconoscimento tardivo ma necessario. Perch脙漏 accorgerci solo oggi che bastava alzare la soglia da 250 a 1000 dipendenti per escludere l'80% delle imprese dall'applicazione della direttiva CSRD sulla rendicontazione di sostenibilit脙聽 ambientale?
La burocrazia 脙篓 come un dazio invisibile: non si paga alla dogana ma ogni giorno pesa sulle imprese, rallenta gli investimenti e blocca la crescita. Il primo Omnibus ritengo che abbia aperto una strada. Ma non bastano le intenzioni: 脙篓 il momento di trasformare le parole in azioni concrete.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T18:37:29"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_63> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_63" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_38> ;
    del:text """Deshalb frage ich mich auch ganz ehrlich: Haben einige Kollegen von Sozialdemokraten und Gr脙录nen noch nicht mitbekommen, wie schlecht es um die europ脙陇ische Wirtschaft steht? Ich finde es wirklich unverantwortlich, wie sich hier einige jedweder Vereinfachung und B脙录rokratieabbau verweigern. Und leider, wenn ich nach Berlin kucke, macht mir das schwarz-rote Sondierungspapier auch nicht sehr viel Hoffnung, dass die Union es tats脙陇chlich ernst meint mit echten Reformen jenseits des Wahlkampfs.
Deswegen mein absoluter Appell an die Kommission: Wir brauchen noch viel mehr Vereinfachung, wir brauchen Abbau von 脙录berfl脙录ssigen Gesetzen und Regulierungen, und deswegen brauchen wir jede Menge neue Omnibusse. Und der n脙陇chste muss ein Digital-Omnibus sein, denn wir m脙录ssen die 脙录berbordenden Digitalgesetze vereinfachen. Wir m脙录ssen endlich bei Innovationen an der Weltspitze sein und nicht bei der Regulierung.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T18:38:52"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_64> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_64" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_39> ;
    del:text """Erst einmal zuvor, liebe Kommissarin: Das ist ein extrem schlechter Stil. Die Tinte von dem Gesetz ist noch nicht mal trocken. Es gibt keinerlei Erfahrung mit diesem Gesetz, ob es 脙录berhaupt zur B脙录rokratie beitr脙陇gt. Unternehmen, die wenden sich an mich und sind total verunsichert. Die haben investiert, die haben Systeme umgebaut. Die B脙录rgerinnen und B脙录rger schreiben mir: Wir wollen keine Kinderarbeit in unserem Kaffee, wir wollen keine Umweltverbrechen in unseren Textilien, und die EU hat uns das garantiert. Und jetzt so ein kurzfristiges, undurchdachtes Hin und Her. Das zerst脙露rt Vertrauen in EU芒聙聭Gesetzgebung.
Und jetzt zweitens zum Inhalt: Die Kommission hatte angek脙录ndigt, Berichtspflichten zur脙录ckzuschrauben. Ja, wir brauchen Entlastungen insbesondere f脙录r kleine und mittelst脙陇ndische Unternehmen. Aber dieser Vorschlag ist keine Entlastung, es ist keine einfache Reduktion von Berichtspflichten. Dieser Vorschlag ist eine massive Deregulierung, die die Ziele des Gesetzes gef脙陇hrdet. Was hat es denn mit Berichtspflichten zu tun, wenn die zivilrechtliche Haftung gestrichen wird? Was hat es mit Berichtspflichten zu tun, wenn Bu脙聼gelder gesenkt werden? Was hat es mit Berichtspflichten zu tun, wenn Unternehmen nur noch den ersten Zulieferer pr脙录fen m脙录ssen, wo doch die meisten Menschenrechtsverletzungen am Anfang der Lieferkette passieren?
Das ist mit uns Gr脙录nen nicht zu machen. Vereinfachung ja, aber keine Deregulierung. In dem Sinne werden wir nachverhandeln.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T18:41:09"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_65> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_65" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_40> ;
    del:text """Komission esitt脙陇m脙陇t muutokset vesitt脙陇v脙陇t esimerkiksi yritysvastuudirektiivin rajaamalla soveltamisalasta ulos pienemm脙陇t alihankkijat sek脙陇 heikent脙陇m脙陇ll脙陇 ihmisoikeusloukkausten uhrien asemaa. Jos huolellisuutta vaaditaan vain ensimm脙陇isess脙陇 tuotantoportaassa, kuten komissio nyt esitt脙陇脙陇, valvotaan esimerkiksi ananasmehun tuotannon ihmisoikeusvaikutuksia jatkossa vain Suomen Kuopiossa, ei Thaimaassa, mist脙陇 alihankintaa tehd脙陇脙陇n.
T脙陇llaisessa s脙陇脙陇ntelyss脙陇 ei ole mit脙陇脙陇n j脙陇rke脙陇, ja se my脙露s tuhoaa t脙陇m脙陇n koko direktiivin alkuper脙陇isen ajatuksen.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T18:43:06"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_66> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_66" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_41> ;
    del:text """Este paquete supone un paso en la direcci脙鲁n correcta, pero a脙潞n hay margen de mejora. La reducci脙鲁n de cargas administrativas debe ir m脙隆s lejos para que las empresas europeas puedan crecer sin obst脙隆culos regulatorios innecesarios. Un ejemplo claro son las obligaciones impuestas por la Directiva sobre informaci脙鲁n corporativa en materia de sostenibilidad que impone a muchas empresas la redacci脙鲁n de informes de sostenibilidad, incluso cuando ya forman parte de grupos empresariales que presentan estos datos de una manera consolidada.
Con el paquete 脙鲁mnibus se han introducido cambios que eliminan redundancias, pero las empresas europeas siguen dedicando muchos recursos a cumplir con exigencias burocr脙隆ticas en vez de centrarse en su negocio. La autonom脙颅a estrat脙漏gica de la que tanto hablamos no ser脙隆 posible si no facilitamos las cosas a quienes producen, innovan y crean riqueza en Europa. Debemos competir en igualdad de condiciones con otras regiones del mundo. Seguimos trabajando para que este paquete sea a脙潞n m脙隆s ambicioso en la eliminaci脙鲁n de cargas administrativas.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T18:44:43"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_67> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_67" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_42> ;
    del:text """The same holds, actually, for the ambition that we had as Commission and Parliament. The Green Deal and the European climate law, those were more than just policies. They formed our vision for a sustainable, innovative and strong Europe. We made a promise to industry, to businesses and to workers, who believed and worked on this vision, that if you innovate, if you invest in green technologies, if you are committed to decarbonise, we will have your back. With stable and predictable legislation, we will help you invest, grow and provide secure jobs that we all need.
And now we are here today. I challenge everyone in this room to explain to me how creating simplification helps us form a robust response to China and other global players. I fear that this so-called vision of competitiveness and simplification is not enough, and it distracts us from the real solutions we need, like a market creation for green and digital European technologies. And I cannot stress this enough. Market creation, not deregulation, market creation, not deregulation. That's what we need. That's what we need to create jobs, to grow our economy and really become competitive.
By simplification, we somehow believe that the investments that we need will pop up, that they will magically appear. As we say in Dutch, costs always come before the profits. It doesn't mean that there are no rules that we can simplify, but emphasising only on this, only on simplification, will not do the job.
And while we focus on this, while we create more uncertainty and step away from our regulatory stability, the world invests in clean tech. China's economy today, its growth is more than 40脗聽% attributed to green investments, and we are failing ourselves to meet the targets that we set, whether it's for cars or whether it's, for example, when it comes to hydrogen for RepowerEU, our strategy to become less dependence on autocrats outside Europe.
I really believe that that is how we could improve our competitiveness, by reaching these targets, by investing in green technologies, by becoming less dependent on energy coming from outside Europe.
We have to create this through regulatory stability. We have to create this by growing these sectors within our market.
Mazzucato, the famous economist, states that in transitions we should not distinguish between winners and losers, but between those who are willing and those who are not. And I fear that we listen to much to companies that are not willing to change and do not see a future in Europe. And by listening to them, we are ignoring innovative companies that can become future tech leaders. Those companies can use a push. We can use a push by creating a green market so that they can have a foot on the ground. That's the question today. Are we supporting them or are we ignoring them? And with that, not creating competitiveness in Europe.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T18:46:22"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_68> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_68" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_43> ;
    del:text "La Commission pr脙漏tend simplifier, mais elle ne fait qu芒聙聶exempter temporairement certaines entreprises de r脙漏glementations excessives, sans remettre en cause la logique bureaucratique qui les sous-tend. Qui peut croire que l芒聙聶on sauvera l芒聙聶industrie europ脙漏enne avec des formulaires? L芒聙聶脗芦omnibus脗禄 ne change rien au fond du probl脙篓me. Ce probl脙篓me, c芒聙聶est la surr脙漏glementation structurelle, qui asphyxie notre 脙漏conomie. Aujourd芒聙聶hui, la mise en conformit脙漏 co脙禄te 3 脙聽 4脗聽% du PIB, et une entreprise europ脙漏enne d脙漏pense 2,5脗聽fois plus en formalit脙漏s qu芒聙聶une entreprise am脙漏ricaine. L芒聙聶脙漏l脙漏phant dans la pi脙篓ce, c芒聙聶est ce bloc de r脙漏glementations vertes, qui nous prive de croissance. Tant que nous ne remettrons pas 脙聽 plat cette machine bureaucratique, ces ajustements resteront anecdotiques." ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T18:49:54"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_69> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_69" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_44> ;
    del:text "Kiedy my tutaj debatujemy, w moim okr脛聶gu, w Janikowie, w powiecie inowroc脜聜awskim, koszt Zielonego 脜聛adu p脜聜ac脛聟 mieszka脜聞cy, samorz脛聟d i pracownicy zak脜聜ad脙鲁w chemicznych, kt脙鲁re za chwil脛聶 zostan脛聟 zamkni脛聶te, a co za tym idzie ca脜聜y 脜聜a脜聞cuszek przedsi脛聶biorstw zostanie zamkni脛聶tych. Ludzie trac脛聟 prac脛聶, a ca脜聜y powiat wkr脙鲁tce b脛聶dzie powiatem widmem. Tak dzia脜聜a Zielony 脜聛ad." ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T18:51:12"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_7> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_7" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1> ;
    del:text """The dates are available on the plenary webpage and the deadlines are as follows: amendments, today at 7脗聽p.m.; roll-call votes, Tuesday, 11脗聽March at 4脗聽p.m. The vote will then take place on Wednesday, 12脗聽March at noon.
芒聛聜
I would like to inform the House that I have received multiple requests for points of order. I will go through them one by one.
First, I give the floor to Ms脗聽Iratxe Garc脙颅a P脙漏rez.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T17:07:20"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_70> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_70" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_45> ;
    del:text """Dus daarom deze vraag: kan de Commissie zich standaard committeren aan het "think small (business) first"-principe in de Europese wetgeving? Daarnaast ben ik geen voorstander van dubbele afspraken, zoals de CSRD en de CSDDD. Daarnaast bestaan de OESO-richtlijnen al jaren, inclusief een handhavingsinstrument via nationale contactpunten.
Wat denkt de Commissie ervan om bestaande internationale afspraken, zoals de OESO-richtlijnen, te hanteren als uitgangspunt? Het Omnibus-voorstel is een goede eerste stap, maar er is nog veel werk aan de winkel. Minder rapportages zijn nodig, want het gaat uiteindelijk om vertrouwen in de ondernemers, om innovatie en concurrentiekracht.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-10T18:52:32"^^xsd:dateTime .

